<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 780/98 of 7 April 1998 amending Regulation (EC) No 1488/96 as regards the procedure for adopting the appropriate measures where an essential element for the continuation of support measures for a Mediterranean Partner is lacking </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 780/98, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1488/96 selles osas, mis k&auml;sitleb asjakohaste meetmete v&otilde;tmise korda, kui m&otilde;ni Vahemere piirkonna partneri toetuseks m&otilde;eldud meetmete j&auml;tkamiseks vajalik tingimus j&auml;&auml;b t&auml;itmata 7. aprill 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 235 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 235, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3 of Council Regulation (EC) No 1488/96 of 23 July 1996 on financial and technical measures to accompany (MEDA) the reform of economic and social structures in the framework of the Euro-Mediterranean partnership (3) provides that the said Regulation is based on the respect for democratic principles and the rule of law and also for human rights and fundamental freedoms, which constitute an essential element thereof, the violation of which element will justify the adoption of appropriate measures; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu 23. juuli 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1488/96 (Euroopa-Vahemere partnerluse raames toimuva majandus- ja sotsiaalstruktuuride reformiga kaasnevate finants- ja tehniliste meetmete (MEDA) kohta) (3) artikliga 3 n&auml;hakse ette, et k&otilde;nealune m&auml;&auml;rus p&otilde;hineb demokraatlike p&otilde;him&otilde;tete, &otilde;igusriigi ning inim&otilde;iguste ja p&otilde;hivabaduste austamisel, mis on selle m&auml;&auml;ruse oluline element ning mille rikkumine annab aluse v&otilde;tta asjakohased meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 16 of Regulation (EC) No 1488/96 provides that the definitive procedure for adopting the appropriate measures where an essential element for the continuation of support measures to a Mediterranean partner is lacking is to be determined by 30 June 1997; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1488/96 artikliga 16 n&auml;hakse ette, et l&otilde;plik kord asjakohaste meetmete v&otilde;tmiseks, kui m&otilde;ni Vahemere piirkonna partneri toetuseks m&otilde;eldud meetmete j&auml;tkamiseks vajalik tingimus j&auml;&auml;b t&auml;itmata, m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks enne 30. juunit 1997; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore necessary to amend Regulation (EC) No 1488/96 to determine such a procedure; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu on vaja muuta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1488/96 ja k&otilde;nealune kord kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Treaty has not provided, for the adoption of this Regulation, powers other than those of Article 235, </inglise>
<eesti> asutamislepinguga ei n&auml;hta k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmiseks ette muid volitusi peale artiklis 235 s&auml;testatute, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Article 16 of Regulation (EC) No 1488/96 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1488/96 artikkel 16 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Article 16 </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 16 </eesti>
<inglise> When an essential element for the continuation of support measures to a Mediterranean partner is missing, the Council may, acting by a qualified majority on a proposal from the Commission, decide upon appropriate measures. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui m&otilde;ni Vahemere piirkonna partneri toetuseks m&otilde;eldud meetmete j&auml;tkamiseks vajalik tingimus j&auml;&auml;b t&auml;itmata, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;ukogu komisjoni ettepanekul kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega teha otsuse vajalike meetmete kohta." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 7 April 1998. </inglise>
<eesti> Luxembourg, 7. aprill 1998 </eesti>
